globalCompletions.name: properties
globalCompletions.description: List of properties of the current Resource.

globalCompletions.name: resolver
globalCompletions.description: The resource resolver associated with the current request

nestedCompletions.name: resource
nestedCompletions.description: The Resource object on whose behalf the servlet acts

nestedCompletions.name: resourceResolver
nestedCompletions.description: The ResourceResolver which resovled the resource of this request

nestedCompletions.name: requestPathInfo
nestedCompletions.description: The RequestPathInfo pertaining to this request

nestedCompletions.name: requestParameterMap
nestedCompletions.description: A `Map` of the parameters of this request

nestedCompletions.name: requestParameterList
nestedCompletions.description: The requests parameters as instances of the `RequestParameter` interface

nestedCompletions.name: responseContentType
nestedCompletions.description: The framework preferred content type for the response. The content type only includes the MIME type, not the character set

nestedCompletions.name: responseContentTypes
nestedCompletions.description: A list of content types which the framework accepts for the response. This list is ordered with the most preferable types listed first. The content type only includes the MIME type, not the character set.

nestedCompletions.name: requestProgressTracker
nestedCompletions.description: The `RequestProgressTracker` for this request

nestedCompletions.name: authType
nestedCompletions.description: The name of the authentication scheme used to protect the servlet.

nestedCompletions.name: cookies
nestedCompletions.description: An array containing all of the `Cookie` objects the client sent with this request.

nestedCompletions.name: headerNames
nestedCompletions.description: An enumeration of all the header names this request contains.

nestedCompletions.name: method
nestedCompletions.description: The name of the HTTP method with which this request was made.

nestedCompletions.name: pathInfo
nestedCompletions.description: Any extra path information associated with the URL the client sent when it made the request

nestedCompletions.name: pathTranslated
nestedCompletions.description: Any extra path information after the servlet name but before the query string, and translates it to a real path.

nestedCompletions.name: contextPath
nestedCompletions.description: The portion of the request URI that indicates the context of the request. The context path always comes first in a request URI.

nestedCompletions.name: queryString
nestedCompletions.description: The query string that is contained in the request URL after the path

nestedCompletions.name: remoteUser
nestedCompletions.description: The login of the user making this request, if the user has been authenticated, or `null` if the user has not been authenticated.

nestedCompletions.name: userPrincipal
nestedCompletions.description: Returns a `java.security.Principal` object containing the name of the current authenticated user.

nestedCompletions.name: requestedSessionId
nestedCompletions.description: Returns the session ID specified by the client. This may not be the same as the ID of the current valid session for this request. If the client did not specify a session ID, this method returns `null`.

nestedCompletions.name: requestURI
nestedCompletions.description: Returns the part of this request's URL from the protocol name up to the query string in the first line of the HTTP request. The web container does not decode this String.

nestedCompletions.name: requestURL
nestedCompletions.description: Reconstructs the URL the client used to make the request. The returned URL contains a protocol, server name, port number, and server path, but it does not include query string parameters.

nestedCompletions.name: servletPath
nestedCompletions.description: Returns the part of this request's URL that calls the servlet. This path starts with a "/" character and includes either the servlet name or a path to the servlet, but does not include any extra path information or a query string.

nestedCompletions.name: session
nestedCompletions.description: Returns the current session associated with this request, or if the request does not have a session, creates one.

nestedCompletions.name: requestedSessionIdValid
nestedCompletions.description: Checks whether the requested session ID is still valid.

nestedCompletions.name: requestedSessionIdFromCookie
nestedCompletions.description: Checks whether the requested session ID came in as a cookie.

nestedCompletions.name: requestedSessionIdFromURL
nestedCompletions.description: Checks whether the requested session ID came in as part of the request URL.

nestedCompletions.name: path
nestedCompletions.description: The absolute path of this resource in the resource tree.

nestedCompletions.name: name
nestedCompletions.description: The name of this resource. The name of a resource is the last segment of the path.

nestedCompletions.name: parent
nestedCompletions.description: The parent resource or `null` if this resource represents the root of the resource tree.

nestedCompletions.name: children
nestedCompletions.description: An iterable of the direct children of this resource.

nestedCompletions.name: resourceType
nestedCompletions.description: The resource type is meant to point to rendering/processing scripts, editing dialogs, etc. It is usually a path in the repository, where scripts and other tools definitions are found, but the ResourceResolver is free to set this to any suitable value such as the primary node type of the JCR node from which the resource is created.

nestedCompletions.name: resourceSuperType
nestedCompletions.description: The super type of the resource if the resource defines its own super type. Otherwise `null` is returned.

nestedCompletions.name: resourceMetaData
nestedCompletions.description: The meta data of this resource.

nestedCompletions.name: resourceResolver
nestedCompletions.description: The ResourceResolver from which this resource has been retrieved.

nestedCompletions.name: valueMap
nestedCompletions.description: A value map for this resource. The value map allows to read the properties of the resource

nestedCompletions.name: index
nestedCompletions.description: zero-based counter `(0..length-1)`

nestedCompletions.name: count
nestedCompletions.description: one-based counter `(1..length)`

nestedCompletions.name: first
nestedCompletions.description: `true` if the current item is the first item

nestedCompletions.name: middle
nestedCompletions.description: `true` if the current item is neither the first nor the last item

nestedCompletions.name: last
nestedCompletions.description: `true` if the current item is the last item

nestedCompletions.name: odd
nestedCompletions.description: `true` if the index is odd

nestedCompletions.name: even
nestedCompletions.description: `true` if the index is even
